<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="99" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="99">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="99">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Leptomias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leptomias globosus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosus">Leptomias globosus</taxonomicName>
is an endemic species of China which recorded from Maerkang, central region of Sichuan (Fig. 24). 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Leptomias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leptomias globosus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosus">Leptomias globosus</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other species by the following characters: disc of pronotum is strongly convex; prothorax broadest in middle; scrobes with dorsal margin not carinate; elytra posterior margin carinate, striae narrow, punctures small, every interstriae with 1-2 column setae, odd interstriae slightly raised than even ones; penis short and robust, apex short and truncate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
